<Base
  title="About"
  description="Canadian Rates is an independent rate-comparison and decision-tools site for Canadian mortgages. Who we are, what we publish, and how we make money."
  canonical="https://canadianrates.ca/about"
>
  <h1>About Canadian Rates</h1>
  <p class="page-meta">Last reviewed May 1, 2026.</p>
  <p>
    Canadian Rates displays publicly-published posted and discounted
    mortgage rates from major Canadian lenders. Both rates come directly
    from each lender's public rates page; we don't estimate or apply a
    haircut. We update daily.
  </p>
  <p>
    We earn a commission when you apply through some lender links. See our
    <a href="/disclosure">affiliate disclosure</a>. How we collect and
    publish rates is documented in full at our
    <a href="/methodology">methodology</a> page.
  </p>
  <h2>Who runs this site</h2>
  <p>
    This site is operated by an independent owner. We do not employ licensed
    mortgage brokers or financial advisors, and the information on this site is
    not personal advice. For personalized recommendations, consult a licensed
    mortgage professional.
  </p>

  <h2>Editorial team</h2>
  <p>
    Guides on this site are written by the Canadian Rates editorial
    team. Content is researched against primary sources (Bank of Canada,
    OSFI, CMHC, lender rate sheets), drafted, edited, and reviewed before
    publication. We do not publish ghostwritten content under fictional
    bylines, and we don't claim credentials we don't have.
  </p>
  <p>
    Every guide shows a "Last reviewed" date. We commit to reviewing each
    guide every quarter and updating immediately when underlying rules change.
    See our <a href="/methodology">methodology</a> for the full process.
  </p>
</Base>

<style>
  .page-meta {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }
</style>
